Abia State Governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, has approved the inauguration of a Judicial Panel of Inquiry to investigate allegations of extra-judicial killings and brutality by security agents in the state. The Governor made this known in a statement made available to DAILY POST by his Honorable Commissioner for Information, Chief John Okiyi Kalu on Monday. He said the composition of the panel is as follows: Retired Justice S N Imo â€“ Chairman, Nwakanma John ,Daniel Chinagozi , Ariwa Zuby ,Eric Ikwuagwu,Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Justice (Secretary) ,Bishop Sunday Onuoha , Comrade John Emejor ,Comrade Nnanna Nwafor and Mrs Doris Ogala. According to him, the Committee will be inaugurated on Friday, October 23, 2020, at Government House, Umuahia, at 1pm.